  "text": "In relation to how rapid response programs are operationalized to ensure that they run smoothly and meet their intended purpose, the available literature is limited. The study by Hartling and colleagues describes contextual factors that influenced rapid review methods [CITATION_1] . These were identified by thematic analysis of the interviews. Two of these contextual factors related to how the program was operationalized and are:",
